title: EU and Greenland politicians remain ‘very cautious’ about Donald Trump despite deal
description: CNN’s International Diplomatic Editor Nic Robertson claims there are still plenty of politicians in Europe and the Nordic region who are “cautious” about dealing with US President Donald Trump.  This is despite the fact that President Trump ruled out military force to take Greenland, instead reaching a framework deal while also reversing tariffs which were set to be imposed in February.  “I think the people here [in Greenland] feel relief that that pressure and threat of becoming American citizens, that seems to be receding into the distance,” Mr Robertson told Sky News Australia.  “But plenty of politicians in Europe and this Nordic region who still are very cautious about dealing with President Trump.”

title: Unemployment rate falls from 4.3 per cent to 4.1 per cent
description: The latest employment numbers for December have been released by the Australian Bureau of Statistics.  According to the ABS, the unemployment rate fell from 4.3 per cent to 4.1 per cent.  Sky News Business Editor Ross Greenwood analyses the latest employment numbers and how they could potentially affect the Reserve Bank’s next interest rate decision.

title: Trump’s Greenland framework deal will likely involve the ‘whole Arctic’
description: CNN Business Editor-At-Large claims US President Donald Trump’s Greenland framework deal will likely be a “wider deal” over the whole Arctic.  “A series of events that we expect in the days ahead will dramatically reduce the tensions,” Mr Quest told Sky News Australia.  “If you were to ask me what I think the deal encompasses, it’s probably a wider deal, not involving sovereignty, but a wider deal over the whole Arctic.”

title: Senior Liberals unleash on ‘pathological liar’ Littleproud who is ‘paralysed by fear’
description: Senior Liberal members from the shadow cabinet have lashed Nationals Leader David Littleproud as a “pathological liar”.  On Thursday morning, David Littleproud announced the exit of the Nationals from the Coalition as a result of the party's division on the hate speech bill.  Senior Liberals have reportedly said Mr Littleproud “flat out lied” and he is “paralysed by fear”.

title: Pro-Hamas vandals destroy historic Melbourne monuments
description: Two monuments in Melbourne have been targeted by pro-Hamas vandals.  The First Pioneer statue, erected in 1871, was torn down and spray-painted with a HAMAS symbol, along with the Separation Monument in Flagstaff Gardens.  Graffiti at the sites included slogans such as “the colony will fall” and “death to Australia”.  Victoria police are investigating what Melbourne's Mayor has described as 'unacceptable'.

title: Sunny Hostin urges alleged criminals arrested by ICE to sue Trump in crazy rant
description: The View co-host Sunny Hostin has claimed that President Trump may have "defamed" alleged criminals arrested by ICE.  This comes after Trump presented mugshots of the alleged offenders to the media during a press conference.  Hostin said she found it "distasteful” and “disgusting" that Trump held up pictures of mostly "Black and Brown people."  She then went on to urge those alleged criminals “defamed” by Trump to sue the US President.  This comes as an immigration officer has been injured in Los Angeles when federal agents attempted to arrest an illegal immigrant.

title: Donald Trump's brutal takedown of Canadian Prime Minister Mark Carney
description: US President Donald Trump has brutally taken down Canada and its Prime Minister Mark Carney.  In his speech at the Global Economic Forum in Davos, Switzerland, Trump called on Canada to “be grateful”.  President Trump said the country “lives” because of the United States and has gotten “a lot of freebies”.  Trump’s address follows a stern and harsh speech from Carney, who was praised for his comments and received a standing ovation.  Carney warned of a “rupture” in global relations, saying that powerful nations are abandoning diplomatic traditions in pursuit of personal interests.

title: Donald Trump humiliates WEF elites during brutal Davos takedown
description: Donald Trump has been on fire at the World Economic Forum in Davos, demolishing the elites, who he says, are taking advantage of the United States.

title: Liberal Party ignored the National Party's ‘concerns’: Bridget McKenzie
description: Nationals Senator Bridget McKenzie discusses the shadow cabinet’s mass resignation after opposing the government’s hate speech legislation.  “Our concerns werent dealt with … our room was very clear, we drafted an amendment of changes to restrict hate group listings,” Ms McKenzie told Sky News Australia.  “What the Liberal Party voted on Tuesday night was not what was presented at the shadow cabinet.  “That was a hard line for our room.”

title: Border Patrol officer injured in LA after illegal immigrant ‘weaponised’ vehicle to evade arrest
description: A US Customs and Border Patrol officer has reportedly been injured in California.  The incident unfolded in the Los Angeles city of Compton.  Law enforcement officers were conducting a targeted operation, allegedly attempting to arrest a man described as a “violent criminal” from El Salvador.  The US Department of Homeland Security claims the suspect “weaponised his vehicle” in an attempt to flee and evade arrest and “rammed” law enforcement.

title: Labor weighs tariffs on Chinese steel
description: The Albanese government is considering imposing tariffs and quotas on fabricated steel imports from China.  Local industries are warning that a surge in cheap Chinese products is pushing manufacturers away.  Treasurer Jim Chalmers told the Financial Review he will ask the Productivity Commission to begin an inquiry into allegations of dumping in the steel industry.

title: Scott Bessent hilariously roasts Gavin Newsom as 'Patrick Bateman meets Sparkle Beach Ken'
description: Treasury Secretary Scott Bessent has ruthlessly mocked California Governor Gavin Newsom in a brutal speech at the World Economic Forum.  On Wednesday, Bessent labelled Newsom “economically illiterate” and likened him to “Patrick Bateman meets Sparkle Beach Ken” during the summit in Davos, Switzerland.  Secretary Bessent warned Newsom that the Trump administration would “crack down on waste, fraud and abuse” in California.  Bessent blasted the governor’s decision to turn down a speech about his economic policies, claiming Newsom’s policies have created a “gigantic budget deficit”.

title: Children among multiple missing in New Zealand landslide
description: Several people, including children, are unaccounted for after a landslide struck a campsite near Mount Maunganui in New Zealand.  Emergency services were called to the holiday park around 9:30 am local time.  Campers have been evacuated, with helicopters assisting search and rescue operations.  Emergency Management Minister Mark Mitchell has confirmed a young girl is among the missing.  Police are urging the public to avoid the area, following earlier evacuations in Punaruku due to severe flooding.

title: The View brutally roasted after Zohran Mamdani ‘lovefest’
description: Sky News Digital Presenter Gabriella Power has roasted ABC’s the View for its ‘total lovefest’ of New York City Mayor Zohran Mamdani.

title: Emmanuel Macron hilariously ‘trolled’ for sunglasses at World Economic Forum
description: Sky News Digital Presenter Gabriella Power has poked fun at French President Emmanuel Macron after he was “trolled” on the internet for wearing sunglasses at the World Economic Forum.
